  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Angola: Quality policy development and strengthening of the national quality infrastructure</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Notwithstanding the positive macroeconomic development and high investments, Angola&#xB4;s national quality infrastructure is still under developed and/or non-existent (i.e. standardization, technical regulations, metrology, etc), and there is a clear lack of national/regional coordination (SADC). This is one of the key factors currently holding back a country that has so much to offer. In order to overcome these obstacles, a full range of activities need to be undertaken in order to strengthen the national quality infrastructure, including the establishment of quality policy, legal framework and institutions, as well as the entering into regional and international trade protocols.</narrative>
  </description>
